data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
This application is designed for the use of book collectors and those who are just interested in keeping track of their own personal library. This program comes with a set password that is included in your welcome package. Please fully read all instructions before continuing.
We apologize for the inconvinince but there is currently no process that will allow you (the user) to save images for your entries through this program. If you would like to see how you can save your own images please click on the "Saving Images" tab look to your handbook.
We thank you for purchasing this product. Please check our website periodically to see if there are any updates available. We hope you enjoy.
--Read.Diana Corporation 2009

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value:
This is the main screen of the program after the you have loaded in your catalogue and images. On the left is a toolbox that has buttons to perform the many functions.
The book information can be sorted in ascending order by title, name, year and genre by clicking the column header you wish to sort.
When an entry is searched the information revelant to the search will be displayed on the main screen in the listbox.

data.name: textBox3.Text
data.value:
Through this program you can make changes to an existing file or create a completely new catalogue. You can also delete a file but you will have to ensure that you also delete its companion image since this will not be automatically done through the program. Please refer to saving images for further instructions.
To make changes you must first select an entry from the list and then click the action you wish to proceed with (if you are creating a new entry you do not have to select anything).
You will be then asked to enter your password, which can be found in the front cover of your welcome package. Please remember that you only have three tries to enter the correct password because then the program will abort and all your work may be lost.

data.name: textBox4.Text
data.value:
In addition to making changes to existing file you may also want to create a different catalogue. To do this select the new tab on the toolbar or from the strip menu up at the top of your screen. You may then continue to add as many entries as you may want.
When you are done filling in information for one entry select "Yes" on the Messagebox if you would like to make another entry. However if you are completed entering data just select cancel. You will now be reminded to save your data right away so that it won't be lost.

data.name: textBox5.Text
data.value:
In order to save your images you will have to do it manually through your own compter and not through this program since this feature is not available in this edition.
Create a folder that will contain all of the images for your one catalogue, save and rename all the images so that they each have a similar name. (ie. CC001, CC002, CC003, etc). This will make it easier to upload them through the program and also when the update software comes out you will not have many problems.
To open your images you first must open your data and then when prompted to open the set image file, instead choose "n" and then search through the compter for your folder. Select this folder and then you are all ready to go.
